QUESTION:In Cangjie code language,How to use ArrayList in Cangjie?
ANSWER:To use the ArrayList type in Cangjie, you need to import the collection package. ArrayList<T> is used to represent an ArrayList type, where T is the element type of the ArrayList and can be any type. ArrayList has excellent capacity for resizing and is suitable for scenarios that require frequent addition and deletion of elements.
In contrast to Array, ArrayList can modify elements in place, as well as add and remove elements in place.import collection.ArrayList
fun main() {
    var list = ArrayList<Int64>()
}

QUESTION:In Cangjie code language,How to access the ArrayList member in Cangjie?
ANSWER:When you need access to all the elements of an ArrayList, you can use a for-in loop to iterate through all the elements of the ArrayList.
When you need to know the number of elements in an ArrayList, you can use the size attribute to get the corresponding information.
When you want to access an element in a single specified location, you can use the subscript syntax to access it (the subscript type must be Int64). The first element of a non-empty ArrayList always starts at position 0. You can access any element of the ArrayList from 0 up to the last position (size - 1 of the ArrayList). Using a negative number or an index greater than or equal to size triggers a runtime exception.
ArrayList also supports the syntax for using Range in subscripts,as detailed in the Array section.//for-in 
import std.collection.*
main() {
    let list = ArrayList<Int64>([0, 1, 2])
    for (i in list) {
        println("The element is ${i}")
    }
}

//know the number of elements 
import std.collection.*
main() {
    let list = ArrayList<Int64>([0, 1, 2])
    if (list.size == 0) {
        println("This is an empty arraylist")
    } else {
        println("The size of arraylist is ${list.size}")
    }
}

//access an element in a single specified location
import std.collection.*
main() {
    let list = ArrayList<Int64>([0, 1, 2])
    let a = list[0] // a == 0
    let b = list[1] // b == 1
    let c = list[-1] // Runtime exceptions
}

QUESTION:In Cangjie code language,How to modify elements in an ArrayList in Cangjie?
ANSWER:You can modify elements in an ArrayList using subscript syntax. Since ArrayList is a reference type, modifications to elements affect all references to the same instance.let list = ArrayList<Int64>([0, 1, 2])
list[0] = 3

let list1 = ArrayList<Int64>([0, 1, 2])
let list2 = list1
list2[0] = 3
// list1 contains elements 3, 1, 2
// list2 contains elements 3, 1, 2
